Shell Oil Co.: The nation's sixth-largest oil company said its second-quarter 
earnings plunged 63% to $161 million on revenue that slipped 12% to $5.2 
billion. Houston-based Shell said the results reflected weakness in all three 
of its businesses -- exploration, oil products and chemicals -- and a writeoff 
of unproductive offshore oil properties. 
