<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA072890-0033 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 253571 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
July 28, 1990, Saturday, San Diego County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Metro; Part B; Page 2; Column 2; Metro Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
168 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST : ESCONDIDO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two 8-year-old Escondido boys, believed missing since early Thursday, were 
still missing Friday, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The boys, Dominic Navarro and Ricardo Sanchez, were last seen when their 
parents dropped them off for school at Central Elementary. 
</P>
<P>
They were not reported missing until the parents returned to pick them up and 
learned they had not attended class that day, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Police were called at 11 p.m. Thursday, after parents checked with family and 
friends. 
</P>
<P>
Both boys are Latino, 40 inches tall and weigh 60 pounds. They have black hair 
and brown eyes. 
</P>
<P>
Navarro was last seen wearing a white T-shirt, black pants, a denim jacket and 
white tennis shoes. He has a scratch on the left side of his face. Sanchez was 
wearing shorts, a black jacket and tennis shoes, according to police. 
</P>
<P>
Lt. John Wilson said foul play is not believed to be involved. 
</P>
<P>
Police said the boys have run away from home on several occasions. Their 
parents believe the boys are staying with friends, police said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
