<HEADLINE>
<P>
CLOSING OF ICE SKATING RINK OPPOSED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
There are only three full-size ice rinks in the Los Angeles area and only two 
with seating for events. 
</P>
<P>
One is going to lose its lease shortly, one is likely to be sold to settle 
family differences, and the third is Pickwick in Burbank. 
</P>
<P>
That a rink that has served the public by providing wholesome activities for 30 
years suddenly is hopeless is unbelievable. 
</P>
<P>
Please join the Save the Ice Committee in helping to keep sports available by 
doing whatever you can to keep Pickwick open. 
</P>
<P>
MARY GRACE CONTRERAS 
</P>
