<HEADLINE>
<P>
WWI GRAVES VANDALIZED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LENS, France 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Vandals broke metal crosses off 38 graves of German soldiers at a World War I 
military cemetery in northern France, police said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
An employee discovered the damage at the Meurchin cemetery near Lens, 124 miles 
north of Paris. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA072890-0071 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 253663 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
