<P>
First baseman Don Mattingly was placed on the New York Yankees' 21-day disabled 
list, but the club said it's too early to write him off for the season. 
</P>
<P>
Asked about Mattingly's chances of playing again this season, Pete Peterson, 
Yankee vice president and general manager, said: "I certainly hope so, let me 
put it that way." 
</P>
<P>
Peterson said the team was waiting to see how Mattingly's back responded to 
rest. 
</P>
<P>
Mattingly, 29, returned to his Evansville, Ind., home Thursday. 
</P>
