MacFarlane, president of Burlington's U.S. subsidiary for the last two years, 
and Peter Thorrington, head of the company's international unit since mid-1988. 
Marshall will remain chairman of Burlington. A Pittson spokesman said Friday 
that this is the first time the company has named joint CEOs at a subsidiary. 
